She is a trained meditation and mindfulness teacher. Her trainings are also influenced by positive philosophy, EFT, and other personal development techniques. 

Vivianne about her trainings: 
"For as long as I can remember, I'm fascinated by what motivates a person in life. I wanted to know what somebody can do to experience more happiness, success and creativity. What can anyone do him/herself to get more fun out of life, despite the circumstances?

Having been searching for the 'ideal' job, the 'ideal' social circumstances, the 'ideal' environment, I found out that happiness is not a destination. It is the little things, the little moments that give you your liveliness. To find these moments you can exercise your mind. You can make a conscious choice to train yourself for more happiness. And once you've made this choice, I'm here to guide you. Happy Mind, Happy Life."

I’m on a mission to dispel the myth that to be healthy one must be thin, or of ‘normal’ weight and that beauty and thinness are important or relevant. I want to help create a world where the conversation about beauty has faded into the background. I want to live in a world where women (and men) can own their power and make their contribution to the world, without feeling guilty for taking up space!
